commit.message:
Only request the BOS descriptor when bcdUSB > 0x0200

See https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-usb-blog/usb-2-1-2-0-1-1-device-enumeration-changes-in-windows-8/ba-p/270775
Close the libusb handle if returning failure from open()

Allow reading HID descriptors larger than 255 bytes

Fixes https://github.com/hughsie/libgusb/issues/114
trivial: Disable the FreeBSD CI target, it's broken again
Show a build error for -Dvapi=true -Dintrospection=false

Use 'iface' as interface is a type in windows.h

This fixes compiling with MinGW when we import gusb.h before the _WIN32 headers.

trivial: Allow loading multiple JSON emulations on the CLI

This allows us to test the hotplug signals.
Fix a buffer over-read when emulating devices
trivial: post release version bump
Release version 0.4.8

Add an device error code for 'busy'

In client code we have to handle it differently from _NO_DEVICE.
trivial: post release version bump
Release version 0.4.7

Add g_usb_device_get_hid_descriptors()

This allows us to get the HID descriptor data.

trivial: Update GitHub Actions versions

Node.js 12 actions are deprecated. These actions are using Node.js 16.

Add calling convention to libusb callback functions

This fixes compiling with clang 16 in 32 bit mingw environment.

Here is the compiler error:
../gusb/gusb-device.c:2298:10: error: incompatible function pointer types passing
'void (struct libusb_transfer *)' to parameter of type 'libusb_transfer_cb_fn'
(aka 'void (*)(struct libusb_transfer *) __attribute__((stdcall))')
[-Wincompatible-function-pointer-types]
trivial: post release version bump
Release version 0.4.6
trivial: Reformat with clang-format
Use project_source_root to fix building as a subproject

Fix BulkTransfer out-of-order reply

The reply to an out-of-order outgoing BulkTransfer may be also out-of-order

Currently we can get:
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x01,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 315
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x82,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 316

found out-of-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x01,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 312
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x82,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 320

while expecting:
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x01,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 315
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x82,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 316

found out-of-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x01,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 312
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x82,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 314

found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x01,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 319
found in-order BulkTransfer:Endpoint=0x82,Data=,Length=0x25 at position 320

Add json_object_get_*_member_with_default() helpers

json library previous to version 1.6.0 doesn't provide the
json_object_get_*_member_with_default() functions.
trivial: post release version bump
Release version 0.4.5
trivial: Fix critical warning when emulating devices

Store the config-index as a GUsbDeviceEvent

This allows emulating the Google Servo Micro.
trivial: Fix critical warning when unloading an emulated device

Record zero-sized device events

These are used for DFU reset operations.
Reset the in-order event index when clearing the event array

Do not emit spurious ::device-removed events when emulating

If we load new emulation data we have to do horrible tricks in the caller to
avoid handling the remove event when loading new event data.

Make the caller (fwupd) much simpler by emitting the correct signals.

Also add a ::device-changed signal that we can use to reload the device events.
